3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Vertex calculates AAVE/USDT funding rates hourly based on the premium between perpetual and spot prices, with payments occurring every hour at minute 0. The platform's cross-margin system allows traders to use USDT collateral across multiple positions, optimizing capital efficiency for multi-pair arbitrage strategies. Funding rates are applied to the notional position size, with longs paying shorts when rates are positive."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","AAVE","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"AAVE perpetuals exhibit significant funding rate volatility due to DeFi governance events, protocol updates, and varying demand between long and short positions. The token's mid-tier volume on Vertex creates opportunities for sustained funding rate premiums without excessive competition from large arbitrageurs."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"AAVE/USDT on Vertex has shown funding rate spikes during major DeFi market movements and AAVE governance proposals. Rates frequently exceed ±0.1% during protocol upgrade announcements or when AAVE lending rates change significantly. The hourly settlement frequency means arbitrageurs can capture these premiums more frequently than 8-hour funding cycles. Weekend periods often see reduced arbitrage activity, leading to sustained funding rate imbalances."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Strategy"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Vertex's low 0.02% maker fees make delta-neutral funding rate strategies highly profitable when AAVE rates exceed 0.05% per hour. The cross-margin system enables efficient hedging across spot AAVE holdings or other perpetual positions. Traders can exploit funding rate divergence between Vertex and centralized exchanges by maintaining opposite positions. The fast sequencer allows rapid position adjustments when funding rates shift, crucial for maximizing capture efficiency."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations and Limitations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Vertex's concentration on Arbitrum creates bridge risks when moving funds for cross-exchange arbitrage strategies. The sequencer's centralized nature introduces potential downtime risks during high volatility periods. AAVE's relatively lower liquidity compared to major tokens means larger positions may experience slippage during emergency exits. Funding rate arbitrage requires active monitoring due to hourly settlements, and gas costs for position management on Arbitrum must be factored into profitability calculations."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often does AAVE funding settle on Vertex?","answer":"AAVE/USDT funding rates settle every hour at the top of the hour on Vertex DEX. This frequent settlement provides more opportunities to capture funding payments compared to traditional 8-hour cycles on centralized exchanges."},{"question":"What makes Vertex suitable for AAVE funding arbitrage?","answer":"Vertex offers exceptionally low 0.02% taker fees and cross-margin functionality, making small funding rate differences profitable. The hybrid DEX architecture provides fast execution while maintaining on-chain settlement for security."},{"question":"Can I hedge AAVE perpetuals with spot positions on Vertex?","answer":"Vertex only offers perpetual futures trading, not spot. For delta-neutral strategies, you'll need to hold spot AAVE on other platforms or use cross-exchange arbitrage with CEXs that offer AAVE spot trading."},{"question":"What are the risks of AAVE funding arbitrage on Vertex?","answer":"Main risks include Arbitrum bridge dependencies, sequencer downtime, lower liquidity causing slippage, and the need for active hourly monitoring. The cross-margin system also creates liquidation risks if other positions move adversely."}]}]
